sidebar.controlNetWeightDesc: Lowered this value if there is a big misalignment between the text prompt and the control image
sidebar.stepsDesc: The number of denoising steps. More denoising steps usually lead to a higher quality image at the expense of slower inference.
sidebar.guidanceScaleDesc: Higher guidance scale encourages to generate images that are closely linked to the text prompt, usually at the expense of lower image quality.
sidebar.maskBlurDesc: Blur the edge of mask area. The higher the number the smoother blend with the original image
sidebar.matchHistogramsDesc: Match the inpainting result histogram to the source image histogram, will improves the inpainting quality for some images.

interactiveSeg.maskExistsDesc: Do you want to remove it or create a new one?
